race.comment: MISSILE SEEKER (4) picked up a Rosehill Midway at nice odds two back then blew the start which put paid to his chances at Randwick last time. Big chance in this company if he decides to put it all together. HOW MUCH BETTER (12) added to his run of minor placings when edged out over 1550m at Canterbury last time out. Back in trip but his seven-furlong stats read well. Maps nicely and will prove tough to hold out. COPACABANA (13) was 29 days between runs which may explain his meek final furlong over 1550m at Canterbury recently. Yet to miss the frame in four runs over 1400m. Better for that last run and can definitely turn things around. HOUSE OF CARDS (9) found 1200m a bit slick at Canterbury last time. Placed three from three here at this distance and he will strip fitter at the third run back from a spell. ROUSSILLON (7) impressed here at this trip last start when coming off a seven-week break for the new stable. Can improve enough to give this a shake.
